    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Little Creepy Crawlers That Will Eat You In the Night</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Cynthia Harrison says Mar 1 article by Michael Lewis on Silicon Valley entrepreneurs refers only to young men, not women (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>What about the young women who dream about entrepeneurship? As encouraging as Lewis's cover story is to those who aspire to find funds and riches in Silicon Valley, and despite his mention of Barbara Hayes-Roth, where are the opportunities for women? While reporting reality is important, so is asking important questions about the future.</p>
        <p>Betty Wong</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
